o? What is the difference between intr_count and local_irq_count[]?<br />&gt; It would be nice if someone knowledgeable could comment on this.<br /><br />Yes, local_intr_count[] is supposed to work on both UP and SMP machines,<br />and 2.1.31 is broken in this regard (your patch is correct). "intr_count" <br />is slowly being phased out: most of the code that uses intr_count is<br />fundamentally broken on any sane SMP implementation.<br /><br />"intr_count" _will_ continue to exist, but it will probably be renamed as<br />"soft_irq_count" or similar, because that is what it currently is used<br />for: software interrupt locking.<br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
